    "en": {
      "title": "Ranil took oath in Parliament",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Ranil Wickramasinghe was sworn in as the 8th Executive President of Sri Lanka.",
        "Speaker Mahinda Yappa Abeywardana welcomed President Ranil Wickremesinghe who visited Parliament.",
        "Following this, Ranil Wickramasinghe was sworn in as the 8th Executive President of Sri Lanka in the presence of Chief Justice Jayantha Jayasuriya.",
        "Ranil Wickremesinghe was appointed as the Prime Minister to fill the vacancy caused by the resignation of former Prime Minister Mahinda Rajapaksa on May 9.",
        "President Gotabaya Rajapaksa stepped down from the presidency on the 14th due to the continued opposition of the people. Following this, Ranil Wickramasinghe, who served as the Prime Minister according to the constitution, was appointed as the Acting President on the 14th.",
        "In this situation, Ranil Wickremesinghe was elected as the new President by getting 134 votes during the secret ballot held in the Parliament yesterday."
      ],
